## 🔑 Part E: Google Maps API Key Setup

1. Go to [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/)
2. Create a new project (or select an existing one)
3. Go to **APIs & Services → Library** and enable:
   - ✅ Maps JavaScript API
   - ✅ Places API
   - ✅ Directions API
   - ✅ Routes API
   - ✅ Geocoding API
4. Go to **APIs & Services → Credentials**
5. Click **Create Credentials → API Key**
6. Copy the API key
7. Open `website/index.html`, find the line near the bottom:
   ```javascript
   key: "AIzaSyAs7evwNLyKLaBI_03MoxFhCHY3MCmTZWo",
   ```
   Replace this with your new API key.

> **Important**: You **must** link a Billing Account to your Google Cloud project. The Directions API requires it even on the free tier. Google gives $200/month of free usage credits.

